ENTRY            33224   20260403   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        33224001   20260403   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 12         35
TITLE      Neutron-induced reaction cross section measurements
            for palladium isotopes at 14.77+/-0.17 MeV with
            covariance analysis
AUTHOR     (R.Kumar, G.T.Bholane, T.S.Ganesapandy, A.B.Khaire,
            F.M.D.Attar, S.S.Dahiwale, V.N.Bhoraskar, S.D.Dhole)
INSTITUTE  (3INDPOO)
           (3INDIND) H.V. Desai College, Pune
           (3INDIND) AKI's Poona College, Pune
REFERENCE  (J,RPC,225,112157,2024)
FACILITY   (CCW,3INDPOO) 14 MeV Neutron Generator
INC-SOURCE (D-T) deuterium ion beam current on 8 Ci tritium target
            was at 175 keV.
SAMPLE     Two PdCl2 samples (99.9% purity) with masses of 0.504 g
            (S1) and 0.510 g (S2) were measured using a
            microbalance ensuring an accuracy of (+/-10 ug).
            Each sample was sealed in a folded polyethylene
            enclosure (~10 mm X 10 mm) to retain recoil nuclei and
            subsequently wrapped in (0.167 g mass, 99.9% pure)
            Al foil serving as a neutron flux monitor.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Relative efficiency of 30% and 1.5 keV energy
            resolution at a gamma energy of 1.33 MeV
METHOD     (ACTIV)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty propagated:
           (MONIT-ERR) Monitor cross section
           (ERR-1) Photopeak counts, sample
           (ERR-2) Photopeak counts, monitor
           (ERR-3) Gamma peak intensities, sample
           (ERR-4) Gamma peak intensities, monitor
           (ERR-5) Isotopic abundance
           (ERR-6) Ratio of efficiencies
           (ERR-7) Time factor, sample
           (ERR-8) Time factor, monitor
STATUS     (TABLE,,R.Kumar+,J,RPC,225,112157,2024) Table 8,10 and
            Text (P.6)
HISTORY    (20260403C) VT
ENDBIB              35
COMMON               2          3
EN         EN-RSL-HW
MEV        MEV
      14.77       0.17
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           42
SUBENT        33224002   20260403   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                  5          5
